ey, France":"Theuley, Haute-Saône, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Noyers","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Lincolnshire): variant of   Bowyer  , with post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Bowyer","meanings":["English: occupational name for a maker or seller of bows, or an archer, from Middle English <i>bowyere</i>, an agent derivative of Old English <i>boga</i> ‘bow’. Compare   Bowman  ."]}]},{"name":"Marguerite","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   Margaret  , also used in the English-speaking world, where its use has been reinforced by the fact that the name was adopted in the 19th century for a garden flower, a large cultivated variety of daisy. <i>Margaret</i> was earlier used in English as a dialect word denoting the ox-eye daisy, and the French equivalent was borrowed into English just in time to catch the vogue for deriving girls' names from vocabulary words denoting flowers.  See also  Daisy ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"De","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Attainment’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Marguerite De Noyers was born about 1305, in France, her father, Miles de Noyers, was 35 and her mother, Jeanne de Dampierre-Flandre, was 19. She married Jean III de Châteauvillain in 1321. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 2 daughters. She died in 1353, at the age of 49."},"et":{"Abt 1305–1353":"umbes 1305–1353","1305–1353":"1305–1353","1305–1361":"1305–1361","1315–1365":"1315–1365","1295–1355":"1295–1355","1325–1389":"1325–1389","1330–1367":"1330–1367","1331–1356":"1331–1356","1271–1350":"1271–1350","1287–1316":"1287–1316","1330":"1330","1350":"1350","1295":"1295","1361":"1361","1271":"1271","Abt 1305":"umbes 1305","1316":"1316","1305"